om Colewick (lost, in Saint Johns in Bedwardine, Worcestershire) or Colewich (Staffordshire), for which see also   Colledge  . The placenames are formed either with the Old English personal name <i>Cola</i> or with Old English <i>col</i> ‘coal, charcoal’ + Old English <i>wic</i> ‘dairy farm’ (see   Wick  ). The surname <i>Colwick</i> is no longer found in Britain. Compare   Collick  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Collick","meanings":["English:","nickname from Middle English <i>collok</i> ‘tankard, bowl, or pail’.","habitational name from any of several places, including Colhook Common in Petworth (Sussex), Colwick in Nottinghamshire (see   Colwick  ), and perhaps a lost or unidentified place in Somerset or Devon."]},{"name":"Colledge","meanings":["English (Midlands and northern England): habitational name from Colwich in Staffordshire, named from Old English <i>col</i> ‘(char)coal’ + <i>wīc</i> ‘building’. The name has become associated with the familiar word <i>college</i>."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir John Colewick was born about 1281, in Colwick, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, William Colewick II, was 35 and his mother, F Colewick, was 34. He married Joan Staunton about 1297, in Colwick, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died after about 1362, in Basford, Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"ABT 1281–Aft 1362":"umbes 1281–umbes pärast 1362","1281–1362":"1281–1362","1281–1335":"1281–1335","1300–1361":"1300–1361","1247–1334":"1247–1334","1249–Female":"1249–Surnud","1362":"1362","1361":"1361","1281":"1281","1280":"1280","23 October 1361":"23. oktoober 1361","1249":"1249","1335":"1335","1247":"1247","1334":"1334","1300":"1300","Abt. 1300":"umbes 1300","Aft 1362":"umbes pärast 1362","about 1297":"umbes 1297","ABT 1281":"umbes 1281","Colwick, Nottinghams